    <header class="article-hero">
      <p class="meta">Gaming · Cybersecurity · 2025</p>
      <h1>Gaming VPN for players: lower ping, DDoS protection and access to global game servers (US market focus)</h1>
      <p class="meta">
        Last updated: <time datetime="2025-12-08">December 8, 2025</time> · Author: Denys Shchur
      </p>
      <figure class="post-hero">
        <img
          src="../../assets/img/hero/vpn-dedicated-ip-uk.webp"
          alt="Gamer using a VPN on laptop with gaming headset, showing global game servers map"
          width="1200"
          height="630"
          class="hero-img"
          fetchpriority="high">
      </figure>
    </header>

    <p>
      Online gaming in the US continues to grow rapidly, but players often struggle with high latency, disruptive DDoS attacks, and regional restrictions on game servers. A <strong><a href="/en-us/blog/what-is-a-vpn.html">gaming VPN</a></strong> offers a strategic advantage for both individual gamers and IT managers supporting multi-state esports teams or gaming platforms. By routing your traffic through optimized servers, a gaming VPN can reduce ping, protect your IP from attacks, and unlock access to game servers worldwide.
    </p>

    <section class="note">
      <strong>Quick note:</strong> A gaming VPN is more than privacy—it’s about <strong>performance, security, and access</strong>. These factors are essential for serious players and organizations managing distributed gaming operations.
    </section>

    <!-- Top CTA -->
    <section class="cta-box">
      <h2>Looking for a gaming VPN that delivers?</h2>
      <p>
        Choose providers with <strong>low-latency servers</strong>, <strong>DDoS protection</strong>, and robust US infrastructure to ensure smooth, secure gameplay.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="https://go.nordvpn.net/aff_c?aff_id=2495&offer_id=312&url_id=2584"
           class="btn btn-primary"
